extraFields.value: The universe starts as a high dimensional state, much higher than the 4 we commonly think of. However, when folded along many axes, one can distinguish a world where three dimensions is possible when looking down the time dimension in a linear fashion. This is where one of many universes can be found.

Because of increased levels of oxygen released by biological life, the ocean was saturated with the poisonous gas. This caused cycles of boom and doom where microscopic life flourished when anoxic and died off in oxygenated conditions. This is shown by patterns of iron banding in rocks. Overall the average temperature of the planet decreased as ozone was added to the atmosphere

While Dianthos was tidally locked, one side of the rocky body was always facing the hot star. It continued to be bombarded with rocks from the solar nebula as dust and rock agglutinated into larger bodies. One significantly large rock named ____ was large enough to slam this planet into a completely different orbital ring around the sun. It drifted for millions of years from its original position in the solar system to its final resting place at 1.38 AU from the sun, making it the second planet in order from closest to farthest.

extraFields.value: After the universe is flipped inside out with all matter being placed into black holes, the universe rescales itself to the size of the largest matter existent. Because of acceleration faster than light speed, it fractures into an infinite number of universes each the size of a handful of quarks. Gluons decay into smaller particles and the extreme mass to space ratio causes opaqueness, then symmetry. This lasts for as long as the universe can stay stable. This universe is a ratio of size smaller than the old universe. Each universe born from the expansion of spacetime is a harmonic resonance below that of the original universe. Unstable universes collapse immediately and continue dropping in scale compared to the original like a water droplet merges with a still pond.

The universe begins in a symmetrical state of matter and antimatter, spacetime and gravity are not possible in this state. There is no time, opacity, or area. 

The ovum is a 57-dimensional object described by a 248-dimensional Lie algebra called E8 .A Lie algebra is a vector space, equipped with an operation called the Lie bracket. A simple example is the set of all 2 by 2 matrices: a 4-dimensional vector space. The Lie bracket operation is [X,Y]=XY-YX.

 It exists in 8 dimensional space with an additional dimension for each of its root vectors. The only type of universe where life as we know it may exist is built on the structure of this type of ovum. Life may only exist in ova with even unimodular lattices. Because of this property, the shape of the ovum is a torus. If seen in 3-space, can be recognized as two concentric 600-cells at the golden ratio. 

Two other likely candidates for life are ova with supersymmetries G3 in 31 dimensions and F4 in 40 dimensions. Given 15 or fewer dimensions, the E8 ovum in 8 dimensions is the only even unimodular lattice (EUL). When considering ova up to 24 dimensions, the only EUL without roots is the Leech ovum.
The E8 ovum has these 4 properties: a trivial center, compact, simply connected, and simply laced.

The event that kickstarted the formation of life from minerals. Spontaneous formation of amino acids by organic compounds. Carbon, nitrogen, phosphorus, methane, water, etc. Creation of RNA follows from this. Natural compositions of lipoid balls and micelles.
First hints of self organization
On earth: only right handed carbohydrates and left-handed amino acids

Natural progression of single-celled life that provides the atmosphere with oxygen. Once the waters had collected enough oxygen, iron began to precipitate out of the water and become Fe (III) which forms patterns in the rocks. This free floating iron could be turned into ferritin and jumpstart the genetic code system of self replication. This replaces the strategy of taxiing around materials to make copies of oneself. Also allows bodies to become more complex.
